verses.roman:
vāṇīnātha, kāśī-miśra prasāda ānila
svahaste sabāre prabhu prasāda khāoyāila

synonyms: vāṇīnātha—Vāṇīnātha; kāśī-miśra—Kāśī Miśra; prasāda ānila—brought all kinds of prasāda; sva-haste—with His own hand; sabāre—unto everyone; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; prasāda—the remnants of the food of Jagannātha; khāoyāila—fed.
translation: Vāṇīnātha Rāya and Kāśī Miśra then brought a large quantity of prasāda, and Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu distributed it with His own hand and fed them all.
